From: bluecat <lmhtq1991@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 28 May 2026 12:00:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Phase C-7 partial: install SIGPROT handler early in StoplessHeap::initialize

C-7's full goal is to bridge stopless_handler into the JVM's crash
handler protocol so the GC's revoke-and-forward path runs *before*
hs_err generation. That's still TODO. This patch lands the minimum
useful piece: install stopless_handler at the start of
StoplessHeap::initialize so that any subsequent SIGPROT yields a
diagnostic line ("[stopless] unforwarded fault: pc=0x...") instead
of being silently killed by the kernel with no hs_err.

Effect: with this patch, the next C-6 cascade SIGPROT
(in JIT/stub-blob code at PC 0x428xxxxx, presumably interpreter
dispatch or pre-generated stub for String::<clinit>) is now
observable; before it was "In-address space security exception"
followed by silent kernel kill (no core, no hs_err).

The handler is the same one used by cap_runtime/stopless_gc/tests/
test_basic — see handler.c. Re-raises with SIG_DFL if no match in
forwarding table (expected during init, since no GC moves yet).

diff --git a/src/hotspot/share/gc/stopless/stoplessHeap.cpp b/src/hotspot/share/gc/stopless/stoplessHeap.cpp
--- a/src/hotspot/share/gc/stopless/stoplessHeap.cpp
+++ b/src/hotspot/share/gc/stopless/stoplessHeap.cpp
@@ -30,7 +30,18 @@ StoplessHeap::StoplessHeap()
     _arena(nullptr) {
 }

+extern "C" int stopless_handler_install(void);
+
 jint StoplessHeap::initialize() {
+  // C-7 partial: install SIGPROT handler EARLY so cap violations
+  // produce a diagnostic instead of a silent kernel-kill SIGPROT.
+  if (stopless_handler_install() != 0) {
+    fprintf(stderr, "[Stopless] WARN: stopless_handler_install failed\n");
+    fflush(stderr);
+  } else {
+    fprintf(stderr, "[Stopless] SIGPROT handler installed\n");
+    fflush(stderr);
+  }
   // v1: no TLAB. Java alloc goes straight through mem_allocate.
   UseTLAB = false;
   // Floor 4 MiB to avoid degenerate small heaps.
